  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen user type the very first char in message input the top bar of chat view always blinks. The same when sending message.\r\nApparently it may be connected to appear-disappearing of the command-image icons located to the left of chat input when the first character appears(disappears) in the input.\r\n\r\nDoesn't happen on Android. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nChat view is static (no blinking behavior when char appears in input)\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nPay attention to the top bar of the chat view:\r\n![ezgif-2-f19d52d6913b](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/111287656-1c938b00-864c-11eb-8905-225a6af5e0a4.gif)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Join any public chat\r\n- Put cursor in message input\r\n- Type any char and pay attention to top chat view bar\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: Develop 1.12 (no issue in release 1.11.1)\r\n- Operating System:  iOS only",
